Game Developer Malang (GDM) is the official web portal for one of Indonesia's most active game development communities. Founded in 2015, the community houses 500+ developers and 12+ indie studios. The platform serves as a central hub for events, studio showcases, and community networking — both locally in Malang and internationally.

---

## Key Features

- **Headless CMS Integration (Keystatic)** — Built with a Keystatic-powered workflow, enabling community leads to manage studio profiles, event schedules, and blog posts without touching the codebase — keeping content fresh and maintenance-free.
- **Studio & Talent Showcase** — A dedicated directory featuring prominent local studios (including Ariverse, Algorocks, and Clay Game Studio), giving each team a professional platform to present their work.
- **Event Management System** — A streamlined interface for promoting major industry events like *Global Game Jam Malang*, with venue details, facilities, and registration links.
- **Hybrid Community Focus** — Designed for both local in-person collaboration in Malang and global online participation via Discord and WhatsApp.
- **Multi-Language Support** — EN/ID localisation to bridge the local community with international industry partners.

---

## Tech Stack

Built with **Next.js** and **Keystatic** (Git-backed headless CMS), providing a fast, secure, and self-maintainable community platform.

---

## Our Contribution

> *"GDM is our community — so we built it like we'd want to use it ourselves. The Keystatic integration means the community can update their own content at any time, without needing a developer. That's the real win."*

This project demonstrates **Ariverse Studio's** commitment to supporting the local game dev ecosystem, and our expertise in building scalable, low-maintenance platforms using modern headless CMS architecture.
